ActOther Than Statutory Authority
SubjectConfirmation of Romaine Indian Reserve No. 2, Quebec
PrecisOrder confirming that 27.679 hectares (68.396 acres) of lands, excluding mines and minerals, have been set apart for the use and benefit of the First Nation of Montagnais de Unamen Shipu as ROMAINE INDIAN RESERVE NO. 2, in Quebec, since February 20, 2008, and continue to be set apart for the Band for that purpose. The land is located in the township of La Gorgendière, some 400 kilometres from the city of Sept-Îles, Quebec.
